Your `BindingContext` is never set, so the bindings have nothing to resolve against.

**Fix — set it in the code-behind:**

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage(MyViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Also ensure your ViewModel raises change notifications:**

```csharp
public class MyViewModel : INotifyPropertyChanged
{
    string _title;
    public string Title
    {
        get => _title;
        set { _title = value; OnPropertyChanged(); }
    }
    // … same for Description

    public event PropertyChangedEventHandler PropertyChanged;
    void OnPropertyChanged([CallerMemberName] string n = null)
        => PropertyChanged?.Invoke(this, new PropertyChangedEventArgs(n));
}
```

> **Tip:** The MVVM Community Toolkit lets you replace all that boilerplate with `[ObservableProperty]` on a field in a `partial class` extending `ObservableObject`.
